              <span id="reviewTextContainer3078865025" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9703435868963876232">Don&apos;t get the wrong idea about this futuristic sci-fi book. Williams (Author) constructs a story about a shape-shifter and AI humanoid who has vengeance. The potential for destruction of the world is always a risk in these novels. Afterall, AI is often programmed one way and acts in another way. It&apos;s a battle between the heroes and villains. Those characters fighting through the worlds with leaders who have no qualms at refusing justice for mayhem. <br/><br/>Drawn into a world that is is a stretch to my i</span>
  <span id="freeText9703435868963876232" style="display:none">Don't get the wrong idea about this futuristic sci-fi book. Williams (Author) constructs a story about a shape-shifter and AI humanoid who has vengeance. The potential for destruction of the world is always a risk in these novels. Afterall, AI is often programmed one way and acts in another way. It's a battle between the heroes and villains. Those characters fighting through the worlds with leaders who have no qualms at refusing justice for mayhem. <br /><br />Drawn into a world that is is a stretch to my imagination and acceptance since sci-fi usually is not my flavor of reading. But I'm attending a sci-fi book group and it was suggested I sample Andrew Williams series to become more at ease with developing situations, shapeshifters, sorcery and action. <br />This is not the first book in the series in fact, you may want to flash back to Arcadia's Children to embrace the full plot and energy behind the author convincingly, skillfully, master novel. </span>
