        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3061073149" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17530435760767590046">Arcadia&apos;s Children: Samantha&apos;s Revenge is an excellent sci-fi novel by the established author, Andrew R Williams. The book has elements of several genres in it, with the most prevalent being science-fiction and fantasy. <br/><br/>Williams is an excellent world-builder and the world he builds in this book is one that the reader can’t help but get lost in. His detailed characters and world-building really help you feel as though you are a part of the novel and once you open those first few pages, you won’t </span>
  <span id="freeText17530435760767590046" style="display:none">Arcadia's Children: Samantha's Revenge is an excellent sci-fi novel by the established author, Andrew R Williams. The book has elements of several genres in it, with the most prevalent being science-fiction and fantasy. <br /><br />Williams is an excellent world-builder and the world he builds in this book is one that the reader can’t help but get lost in. His detailed characters and world-building really help you feel as though you are a part of the novel and once you open those first few pages, you won’t be able to put the book down anytime soon. <br /><br />The book’s central narrative is also brilliant, expertly working in elements from several different genres. The writing is also incredibly compact and the book flies along at an excellent pace. <br /><br />Arcadia's Children: Samantha’s Revenge is the ideal book for those who like their books to be slightly more fantastical and experimental and who want to explore a whole new world. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17530435760767590046" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


