        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3043711355" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3112678041345956859">I was in the mood for some sci-fi as it was a while since I’d read any. Instead of going for one of the more mainstream titles I wanted to give something different a try, and was intrigued by this book from Andrew R. Williams. It was the cover that initially caused me to pause and read more as it has a certain surreal quality to it, but the blurb was enough to win me over and give it a read. Williams has created an extraordinary world with some very vivid imagery and a compelling, but not unnece</span>
  <span id="freeText3112678041345956859" style="display:none">I was in the mood for some sci-fi as it was a while since I’d read any. Instead of going for one of the more mainstream titles I wanted to give something different a try, and was intrigued by this book from Andrew R. Williams. It was the cover that initially caused me to pause and read more as it has a certain surreal quality to it, but the blurb was enough to win me over and give it a read. Williams has created an extraordinary world with some very vivid imagery and a compelling, but not unnecessarily complicated sci-fi story. I hate when authors get bogged down in minutiae in science fiction. But that isn’t the case here.<br /><br />All in all a very enjoyable read and I’ll progress with book two at a later date. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3112678041345956859" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

