<div id="review_3151598688" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3151598688" />
    <a title="Cup and Saucer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/108798963-cup-and-saucer"><img alt="Cup and Saucer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1579176005p2/108798963.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3151598688?book_show_action=true">Jan 20, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cup and Saucer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cup and Saucer" href="/user/show/108798963-cup-and-saucer">Cup and Saucer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3151598688" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer498191019628015154">If you enjoy the Sci-Fi novels of Iain M. Banks then &apos;Arcadia&apos;s Children: Samantha&apos;s Revenge&apos; by Andrew R. Williams is a book that you&apos;re sure to enjoy. The levels of imagination of the author are off the chart, but he has such a great attention to detail, that you can visualise the weird and wonderful worlds and entities he describes to you.<br/><br/>A shape-shifter and a psychic ex-cop are brought together by Samantha – and AI humanoid intent on revenge. Her quest for revenge may bring an end to the uni</span>
  <span id="freeText498191019628015154" style="display:none">If you enjoy the Sci-Fi novels of Iain M. Banks then 'Arcadia's Children: Samantha's Revenge' by Andrew R. Williams is a book that you're sure to enjoy. The levels of imagination of the author are off the chart, but he has such a great attention to detail, that you can visualise the weird and wonderful worlds and entities he describes to you.<br /><br />A shape-shifter and a psychic ex-cop are brought together by Samantha – and AI humanoid intent on revenge. Her quest for revenge may bring an end to the universe, troubled ex-cop Tarmy and the resurrected Claire Hyndman can thwart her plans.<br /><br />It is fantastical, engrossing, gripping, exciting, and creepy. It has everything a good Sci-Fi novel needs and then some. It's unpredictable and fantastical, with plot twists I never saw coming. I would love to see this brought the the big or small screen, but until that happens, I will move on to the next in the series.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="498191019628015154" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


